  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently in the latest develop we change the IPC path based on the datadir. This makes not much sense as the Unix socket path should always be the same path, so any application can connect to any running node.\n\nE.g. if you change your datadir to an external harddrive, the unix socket IPC wouldn't work from there anymore, due to OS restrictions.\n\nSo there is not much sense in moving the IPC path based on the datadir.\n\nWhat came out of the idea to move it to `/tmp/ethereum.ipc` ?\n",
