    "body": "I don't :P\n\nThis comes crumbling down when you want to run multiple instances on the same computer, which is further complicated when you have an instance running, want to develop on another and maybe run some tests concurrently which fire up the IPC. Most people will run geth with the defaults, so I don't think this is much of an issue, and if it is, then make sure the tools can handle a different path.\n\nHaving a global singleton master path is imho a very bad design decision. Imagine that I have a geth instance working for public apps, and a private instance. I forget by accident to explicitly set the IPC path too for the private instance, and all of a sudden all my apps poke around in my private chain.\n\nI would much rather have sane defaults that play nice together with different scenarios. \n",
