    "body": "Also various platforms have a ton of restrictions on where you have permissions for what. Within the datadir is usually a safe starting bet that the correct user can access it, others cannot and that the user actually has permission to open a socket there.\n\nThere are linux distros that have limited access to `tmp`, I've seen OSX versions which use custom `tmp` folders for certain apps to sandbox them, it may not even be a bindable path. Android is again a very strange beast on this front.\n\nLets not dumb down geth to avoid having Mist implement a path selection :P \n",
